<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,749,680,707]" box="[151,749,680,707]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,749,680,707]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,749,680,707]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herrich-Schäffer" authorityYear="1850" box="[151,417,680,706]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Leucochimona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagora">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,417,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Leucochimona lagora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Herrich-Schäffer, [1853])
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,344,751,776]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Natural history.</emphasis>
Adults were never observed openly perching as the three preceding species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1264,1390,753,776]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Mesosemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1264,1390,753,776]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Mesosemia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but only making short flights and alighting on the underside of leaves. Females were observed occasionally flying around host plants and ovipositing during the late morning hours. Eggs were laid singly on the underside of a mature host plant leaf. Larvae cut a circle around the micropylar area to leave the egg. First and second instars fed on the adaxial leaf surface cutting channels and leaving little windows of the upper leaf epidermis intact (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,895,920]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). Three host plants were recorded: 
<taxonomicName box="[548,693,932,957]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="caerulea">
<emphasis box="[548,693,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ps. caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[712,928,932,957]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Palicourea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis box="[712,928,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Palicourea deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC) Borhidi and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borhidi. Gallard" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Aubl." box="[1159,1318,933,956]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Palicourea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis box="[1159,1318,933,956]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Pa. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Pupation occurred on the host plant on stems or leaves. Two color morphs were observed: a dark form with dark brown wing pads (n = 3), and a light form with white wing pads and brown margins (n = 3). Development from egg to adult averaged 39 days.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,636,1076,1101]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Description of immature stages. Egg</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[653,790,1076,1101]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 93–94</figureCitation>
). Embryonic development 9 days (n = 2). Diameter 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.51">0.51 mm</quantity>
(n = 5). Pale yellow-cream when freshly laid, spherical with a flat bottom and a pattern of small hexagons cells armed with small spines on the rib intersections. Micropylar area centered on the top.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1183,1208]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">First instar</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[351,434,1183,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
). Duration 3–4 days (n = 5). Head capsule width 
<quantity box="[1003,1163,1183,1208]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.27" valueMax="0.28" valueMin="0.26">0.26-0.28 mm</quantity>
(n = 5). Newly hatched larvae are approximately 
<quantity box="[441,531,1220,1244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
, maximum length 
<quantity box="[745,814,1220,1244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
. Head capsule light tan, stemmata black; body whitish and dorsally green from the intestinal content. Dorsal setae on each segment dark brown; the lateral setae whitish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,362,1292,1317]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Second instar</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[377,459,1292,1317]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
). Duration 3 days (n = 2). Head capsule width 
<quantity box="[989,1091,1292,1317]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.54">0.54 mm</quantity>
, maximum body length 
<quantity box="[1364,1433,1292,1316]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
. Color pattern and morphology similar to first instar, but with more numerous and larger setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1364,1389]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Third instar.</emphasis>
Duration 3 days (n = 2). Head capsule width 
<quantity box="[864,966,1364,1388]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.84">0.84 mm</quantity>
, maximum body length 
<quantity box="[1239,1308,1364,1388]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Head light tan, body greenish with black setae dorsally and white setae laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,1436,1461]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fourth instar</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[374,455,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
). Duration 4 days (n = 5). Head capsule width 
<quantity box="[977,1078,1436,1461]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="1.15">1.15 mm</quantity>
, maximum length 
<quantity box="[1286,1367,1436,1460]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
. Head light tan; body medium green with black setae dorsally and white setae laterally; spiracles white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,408,1508,1533]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fifth (last) instar</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[425,577,1508,1533]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 98–100</figureCitation>
). Duration 5 days, 3 days feeding and 2 as prepupa (n = 5). Head capsule width 
<quantity box="[222,311,1544,1568]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
, light green, stemmata black. Maximum body length 
<quantity box="[914,996,1544,1568]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
. Dorso yellowish-green during feeding (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1580,1605]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
), prepupa turning darker green with white spots and a rosy coloration on the lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1263,1348,1580,1605]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
). TNOs are a contrasting lighter green on A8 (
<figureCitation box="[577,675,1615,1640]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,751,1928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,261,1652,1677]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Pupa</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,437,1652,1677]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 101–104</figureCitation>
). Duration 11–12 days (n = 5). Length 
<quantity box="[872,1034,1652,1677]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.16" metricValueMax="1.26" metricValueMin="1.06" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="11.6" valueMax="12.6" valueMin="10.6">10.6–12.6 mm</quantity>
(n = 7), width at A2 = 
<quantity box="[1288,1377,1652,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
. Two color morphs were observed. Two days after pupation the wing pads turned from green to either white or dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[237,402,1724,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–104" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,183,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[156,1430,183,1629]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 93–104. Immature stages of Leucochimona lagora. 93, recently oviposited egg; 94, larva emerging from egg; 95, first instar; 96, second instar channeling leaf underside (arrows); 97, fourth instar in lateral view; 98, fifth (last) instar in dorsal view; 99, prepupa; 100, detail of segment A8 in dorsal view in the last instar, arrow indicating tentacle nectary organs (TNO); 101, pupa, individual with light wing case; 102, pupa, with dark wing case; 103, pupa in dorsal view; 104, pupa in ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610274/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 101–102</figureCitation>
). Body color green. Anterior edge of prothorax medium brown followed by a white irregular band. Mesothorax with a pair of reddish brown tubercles. Metathorax with a pair of anterior dark brown spots. A2 crested, anterior green, crest gold-brown. Spiracle of A2 raised and slit-shaped. On A4–A8, lateral area below spiracles black; spiracles white. Segments A9 to A10 red brownish dorsally. Short upright setae on thoracic segments, pointing posteriorly on abdomen. Longer setae on A2 crest and T2 tubercles. Eyes setose. Silk girdle passes over A1 or A2.
</paragraph>
